---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Two Strengths';
const subtitle = 'Storage strength climbs and never falls. Retrieval strength fluctuates. Forgetting is loss of access, not loss of trace.';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude">
    <p class="essay-kicker">Etude · Memory</p>
    <h1>{title}</h1>
    <p class="essay-sub">{subtitle}</p>
    <div class="essay-meta">
      <a href="/essays/memory-was-never-about-storage/">← back to essay</a>
    </div>
    <hr />

    <p>A memory has two strengths, not one. <em>Storage strength</em> only ever rises — once a trace is laid, it stays. <em>Retrieval strength</em> drifts: high after study, low after a week away, high again the moment you find the trace under load. Play the controls below and watch the two curves separate.</p>

    <div class="bars">
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">Storage <span id="store-num">10%</span></div>
        <div class="bar-track"><div id="store-bar" class="bar-fill bar-store" style="width:10%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">Retrieval <span id="retr-num">10%</span></div>
        <div class="bar-track"><div id="retr-bar" class="bar-fill bar-retr" style="width:10%"></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="askers">
      <button type="button" id="study" class="ask-btn">Study the material</button>
      <button type="button" id="wait" class="ask-btn">Wait a week</button>
      <button type="button" id="test" class="ask-btn">Test yourself</button>
      <button type="button" id="reset" class="ask-btn ask-btn-quiet">Reset</button>
    </div>

    <div class="graph-wrap">
      <svg id="graph" viewBox="0 0 320 120" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-label="Storage and retrieval over time">
        <line x1="0" y1="0" x2="320" y2="0" class="axis" />
        <line x1="0" y1="120" x2="320" y2="120" class="axis" />
        <polyline id="store-line" class="line line-store" points="" />
        <polyline id="retr-line" class="line line-retr" points="" />
      </svg>
      <div class="legend"><span class="dot dot-store"></span> storage <span class="dot dot-retr"></span> retrieval</div>
    </div>

    <hr />

    <p>Forgetting isn't loss of trace. It's retrieval drift. Test yourself near the bottom of the curve, and the trace gets stronger — that's spaced repetition, desirable difficulty, the testing effect, all the same finding.</p>
    <p class="essay-detail">Background: Bjork &amp; Bjork's <a href="https://bjorklab.psych.ucla.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2016/07/RBjork_EBjork_1992.pdf">New Theory of Disuse</a> (1992) — every memory carries a storage strength and a retrieval strength, and the gap between them is where learning happens.</p>
  </article>
</Base>

<script is:inline>
  let store = 10;
  let retr = 10;
  const history = [{ s: store, r: retr }];
  const MAX = 12;

  const clamp = (v) => Math.max(0, Math.min(100, v));

  function render() {
    document.getElementById('store-bar').style.width = store + '%';
    document.getElementById('retr-bar').style.width = retr + '%';
    document.getElementById('store-num').textContent = Math.round(store) + '%';
    document.getElementById('retr-num').textContent = Math.round(retr) + '%';

    const pts = history.slice(-MAX);
    const n = pts.length;
    const step = n > 1 ? 320 / (n - 1) : 0;
    const sLine = pts.map((p, i) => `${(i * step).toFixed(1)},${(120 - p.s * 1.2).toFixed(1)}`).join(' ');
    const rLine = pts.map((p, i) => `${(i * step).toFixed(1)},${(120 - p.r * 1.2).toFixed(1)}`).join(' ');
    document.getElementById('store-line').setAttribute('points', sLine);
    document.getElementById('retr-line').setAttribute('points', rLine);
  }

  function step(action) {
    if (action === 'study') {
      store = clamp(store + 10);
      retr = clamp(retr + 10);
    } else if (action === 'wait') {
      retr = clamp(retr - 20);
    } else if (action === 'test') {
      const bonus = retr < 30 ? 8 : 5;
      store = clamp(store + bonus);
      retr = 90;
    }
    history.push({ s: store, r: retr });
    if (history.length > MAX * 2) history.splice(0, history.length - MAX * 2);
    render();
  }

  document.getElementById('study').addEventListener('click', () => step('study'));
  document.getElementById('wait').addEventListener('click', () => step('wait'));
  document.getElementById('test').addEventListener('click', () => step('test'));
  document.getElementById('reset').addEventListener('click', () => {
    store = 10; retr = 10;
    history.length = 0;
    history.push({ s: store, r: retr });
    render();
  });
  render();
</script>

<style>
  .etude { max-width: 38rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.25rem 4rem; }
  .etude h1 { font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 2rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .essay-sub { font-style: italic; color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .bars {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
    background: var(--bg-soft, rgba(0,0,0,0.03));
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .bar-row { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
  .bar-label {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .bar-track {
    height: 0.6rem;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.07);
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .bar-fill {
    height: 100%;
    transition: width 450ms ease;
  }
  .bar-store { background: var(--accent); }
  .bar-retr { background: #5a7a8c; }
  .askers { display: flex; gap: 0.6rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 1.25rem 0; }
  .ask-btn {
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    border-radius: 3px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 100ms;
  }
  .ask-btn:hover { background: rgba(138, 52, 32, 0.08); }
  .ask-btn-quiet { border-color: var(--muted); color: var(--muted); }
  .graph-wrap {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-soft, rgba(0,0,0,0.03));
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  #graph { width: 100%; height: 120px; display: block; }
  .axis { stroke: rgba(0,0,0,0.1); stroke-width: 1; }
  .line { fill: none; stroke-width: 1.6; transition: all 250ms ease; }
  .line-store { stroke: var(--accent); }
  .line-retr { stroke: #5a7a8c; stroke-dasharray: 3 2; }
  .legend {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .dot { display: inline-block; width: 0.55rem; height: 0.55rem; border-radius: 50%; margin-left: 0.4rem; }
  .dot-store { background: var(--accent); }
  .dot-retr { background: #5a7a8c; }
  .essay-detail { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; }
</style>
